org.conqat.lib.commons.assessment.external

Interface IRatingTableFileAccessor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultRatingTableFileAccessor

    public interface IRatingTableFileAccessor
    Interface used to access external rating information.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getFilePath()
      Provides the path corresponding to the rated content.
      java.lang.String getRelativeFileContent(java.lang.String relativePath)
      Returns the content of a file.
      void setRelativeFileContent(java.lang.String relativePath, java.lang.String content)
      Sets the content of a file.

    • Method Detail

      • getFilePath

        java.lang.String getFilePath()
        Provides the path corresponding to the rated content. This does not have to be an actual file's path, but the returned string has to be path-like, i.e. consist of parts separated by slash or back-slash.

      • getRelativeFileContent

        java.lang.String getRelativeFileContent(java.lang.String relativePath)
        Returns the content of a file.
        Parameters:
        relativePath - the path identifying the file, relative to getFilePath(). The path uses the usual ".." notation for parent directories and uses a forward slash as a separator.
        Returns:
        the content or null in case of errors.

      • setRelativeFileContent

        void setRelativeFileContent(java.lang.String relativePath,
                            java.lang.String content)
        Sets the content of a file. This is fail-silent, i.e. in case of an error, just nothing happens.
        Parameters:
        relativePath - the path identifying the file, relative to getFilePath(). The path uses the usual ".." notation for parent directories and uses a forward slash as a separator.
        content - the new content for the file.
